er-url=https://www.questia.com/PM.qst?a=o&d=1072378 |accessdate=April 12, 2010 |publisher=Dodd, Mead |location=New York City |year=1935 |origyear=First published 1935 |oclc=312581 |isbn=1-931313-85-7}}{{Subscription required}}\n*{{cite book|last=Hinsdale|first=Mary Louise |title=A History of the President's Cabinet|publisher=G. Wahr|url=https://archive.org/details/ahistorypreside00hinsgoog|page=[https://archive.org/details/ahistorypreside00hinsgoog/page/n221 207]|year=1911|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |ref=Howe |last=Howe |first=George Frederick |title=Chester A. Arthur A Quarter-Century of Machine Politics |publisher=Frederick Unger Publishing Co |location=[[New York City|New York]], [[New York State|New York]] |year=1935}}\n*{{cite book |last=Hutton |first=Paul Andrew, Ph.D. |authorlink=Paul Andrew Hutton |title=Phil Sheridan and his Army |year=2009 |origyear=First published 1985 |isbn=978-0-8032-2329-5|oclc=10694656 |publisher=University of Oklahoma Press |location=[[Norman, Oklahoma]] |pages=262\u2013266 |chapter-url=https://books.google.com/?id=Spck92Ba2GwC&pg=PA262&dq=President+Grant+sends+Sheridan+to+Louisiana&cd=7#v=onepage&q= |accessdate=February 25, 2010 |chapter=Chapter 12: Reconstructing Louisiana: 'To Charge upon the Liberties of His Fellow-Citizens' |ref=hutton}}\n*{{cite journal |last=Johnson |first=Benjamin S. |title=The Brooks-Baxter War |pages=122\u2013168 |journal=Publications of the Arkansas Historical Association |volume=2 |publisher=Arkansas Historical Association |location=[[Little Rock, Arkansas]] |editor=John Hugh Reynolds |year=1908 |url=https://books.google.com/?id=qxMUAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA122&dq=Brooks-Baxter+War&cd=1#v=onepage&q=Brooks-Baxter%20War |accessdate=February 26, 2010 |oclc=13681571}}\n*{{cite book |last=Kahan|first=Paul|title=The Presidency of Ulysses S. Grant: Preserving the Civil War's Legacy|publisher=Westholme Publishing, LLC|location=Yardley, Pennsylvania|date=2018|ref=harv|isbn=978-1-59416-273-2}}\n*{{cite book|last=Keith |first=LeeAnna |title=The Colfax Massacre: The Untold Story of Black Power, White Terror, & The Death of Reconstruction |publisher=Oxford University Press |location=New York City |page=[https://archive.org/details/colfaxmassacreun00keit/page/100 100] |chapter=Chapter 7: Battle of the Colfax Courthouse |isbn=978-0-19-531026-9 |oclc=145145411 |chapter-url=https://archive.org/details/colfaxmassacreun00keit/page/100 |accessdate=April 13, 2010 |year=2007 }}\n*{{cite web |last=Kennedy |first=Robert C. |title=George M. Robeson |publisher=Dvrbs.com |year=2001 |accessdate=April 13, 2010 |url=http://www.dvrbs.com/people/CamdenPeople-GeorgeMRobeson.htm}}\n*{{cite book |last=Kinley |first=David|title=The Independent Treasury of the United States and its Relations to the Banks of its Country |publisher=U.S. National Monetary Commission, United States Senate |location=Washington, D.C. |year=1910 |chapter=Chapter VIII \u2013 Treasury Relief in Crises, 1873 to 1890 |chapter-url=https://books.google.com/?id=4MAZAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA225&dq=Panic+of+1873#v=onepage&q=Panic%20of%201873 |accessdate=February 2, 2010 |pages=225\u2013235 |oclc=474950853}}\n*{{cite book|last=Kremer |first=Gary R. |title=James Milton Turner and the Promise of America \u2013 The Public Life of a Post-Civil War Black Leader |publisher=University of Missouri Press |location=[[Columbia, Missouri]] |year=1991 |chapter-url=https://archive.org/details/jamesmiltonturne00krem/page/81 |accessdate=January 30, 2010 |isbn=978-0-8262-0780-7 |oclc=23144878 |page=[https://archive.org/details/jamesmiltonturne00krem/page/81 81] |chapter=Chapter V: The Preservation of a Noble Experiment }}\n*{{cite book |last=Lane |first=Charles |authorlink=Charles Lane (journalist) |title=The Day Freedom Died: The Colfax Massacre, the Supreme Court, and the Betrayal of Reconstruction |publisher=Henry Holt and Company |location=New York City |year=2008 |page=[https://archive.org/details/dayfreedomdiedco00lane/page/124 124] |chapter=Chapter Six: Black-Letter La