{"title_page": "Clayton Hospital", "text_new": "{{Short description|Hospital in West Yorkshire, England}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Use British English|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox hospital\n| Name        = Clayton Hospital\n| Org/Group   = [[The Mid Yorkshire Hospitals NHS Trust]]\n| Image       = Clayton Hospital - Wentworth Street - geograph.org.uk - 660907.jpg\n| Caption     = Clayton Hospital\n| Location    = Wentworth Street, [[Wakefield]]\n| Region      = \n| State       = West Yorkshire\n| Country     = England\n| Coordinates = {{Coord|53.6879|-1.5031|display=inline,title}}\n| HealthCare  = NHS\n| Type        = \n| Speciality  = <!-- Only if especially notable -->\n| Emergency   = No\n| Founded     = 1787\n| Closed      = \n| Website     =\n| Wiki-Links  = <!-- optional -->\n| map_type    = West Yorkshire\n| map_caption = Shown in West Yorkshire\n}}\n'''Clayton Hospital''' was a health facility in Wentworth Street, [[Wakefield]], [[West Yorkshire]], England. It was managed by [[The Mid Yorkshire Hospitals NHS Trust]].\n\n==History==\nThe facility had its origins in the Wakefield General Dispensary established in Dispensary Yard in 1787.<ref name=na>{{cite web|url=https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/hospitalrecords/details.asp?id=687|title=Clayton Hospital, Wakefield|publisher=National Archives|accessdate=28 January 2020}}</ref> After Thomas Clayton, a former mayor, decided to finance expansion of the facility, it moved to a site at the junction of Wood Street and Cross Street in 1854.<ref name=plaque>{{cite news|url=https://www.wakefieldexpress.co.uk/news/plaque-marks-wakefield-s-clayton-hospital-site-1-8888165|title=Plaque marks Wakefield\u2019s Clayton Hospital site|newspaper=Wakefield Express|date=1 December 2017|accessdate=28 January 2020}}</ref> It absorbed patients from the Wakefield House of Recovery which closed at that time.<ref name=na/> It was renamed the Clayton Hospital and Wakefield General Dispensary in 1863 to reflect the completion of a new inpatients wing.<ref name=plaque/>\n\nUsing finance from a legacy left by Thomas Clayton, it relocated to new premises in Northgate, designed by William Bakewell, in 1879.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://historicengland.org.uk/images-books/photos/item/BL05546|title=Exterior view from the street showing the centre tower of the Clayton Hospital|publisher=Historic England|accessdate=28 January 2020}}</ref> It joined the [[National Health Service]] as Clayton Hospital in 1948.<ref name=na/> After services had transferred to [[Pinderfields Hospital]], it closed in 2012.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.wakefieldexpress.co.uk/news/historic-clayton-hospital-to-close-1-5020650|title=Historic Clayton Hospital to close|newspaper=Wakefield Express|date=12 October 2012|accessdate=28 January 2020}}</ref> A major fire took place at the derelict hospital in February 2017.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.yorkshireeveningpost.co.uk/news/investigation-launched-cause-fire-old-hospital-building-wakefield-604520|title=Investigation launched into cause of fire at old hospital building in Wakefield|newspaper=Yorkshire Evening Post|date=20 February 2017|accessdate=28 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2017 [[Queen Elizabeth Grammar School, Wakefield]] secured planning consent to refurbish the Victorian Tower but demolish the remainder of the buildings to create sports facilities.<ref>{{cite news|url=\nhttps://www-wakefieldexpress-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org/v/s/www.wakefieldexpress.co.uk/news/grammar-school-to-redevelop-the-former-clayton-hospital-1-8663038/amp?amp_js_v=a2&amp_gsa=1&usqp=mq331AQCKAE%3D#aoh=15802919455179&referrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com&amp_tf=From%20%251%24s&ampshare=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wakefieldexpress.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fgrammar-school-to-redevelop-the-former-clayton-hospital-1-8663038|title=Grammar school to redevelop the former Clayton Hospital|date=21 July 2017|newspaper=Wakefield Express|accessdate=28 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:1787 establishments in England]]\n[[Category:Hospital buildings completed in 1879]]\n[[Category:Hospitals in West Yorkshire]]\n[[Category:Defunct hospitals in England]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|Hospital in West Yorkshire, England}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Use British English|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox hospital\n| Name        = Clayton Hospital\n| Org/Group   = [[The Mid Yorkshire Hospitals NHS Trust]]\n| Image       = Clayton Hospital - Wentworth Street - geograph.org.uk - 660907.jpg\n| Caption     = Clayton Hospital\n| Location    = Wentworth Street, [[Wakefield]]\n| Region      = \n| State       = West Yorkshire\n| Country     = England\n| Coordinates = {{Coord|53.6879|-1.5031|display=inline,title}}\n| HealthCare  = NHS\n| Type        = \n| Speciality  = <!-- Only if especially notable -->\n| Emergency   = No\n| Founded     = 1787\n| Closed      = \n| Website     =\n| Wiki-Links  = <!-- optional -->\n| map_type    = West Yorkshire\n| map_caption = Shown in West Yorkshire\n}}\n'''Clayton Hospital''' was a health facility in Wentworth Street, [[Wakefield]], [[West Yorkshire]], England. It was managed by [[The Mid Yorkshire Hospitals NHS Trust]].\n\n==History==\nThe facility had its origins in the Wakefield General Dispensary established in Dispensary Yard in 1787.<ref name=na>{{cite web|url=https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/hospitalrecords/details.asp?id=687|title=Clayton Hospital, Wakefield|publisher=National Archives|accessdate=28 January 2020}}</ref> After Thomas Clayton, a former mayor, decided to finance expansion of the facility, it moved to a site at the junction of Wood Street and Cross Street in 1854.<ref name=plaque>{{cite news|url=https://www.wakefieldexpress.co.uk/news/plaque-marks-wakefield-s-clayton-hospital-site-1-8888165|title=Plaque marks Wakefield\u2019s Clayton Hospital site|newspaper=Wakefield Express|date=1 December 2017|accessdate=28 January 2020}}</ref> It absorbed patients from the Wakefield House of Recovery which closed at that time.<ref name=na/> It was renamed the Clayton Hospital and Wakefield General Dispensary in 1863 to reflect the completion of a new inpatients wing.<ref name=plaque/>\n\nUsing finance from a legacy left by Thomas Clayton, it relocated to new premises in Northgate, designed by William Bakewell, in 1879.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://historicengland.org.uk/images-books/photos/item/BL05546|title=Exterior view from the street showing the centre tower of the Clayton Hospital|publisher=Historic England|accessdate=28 January 2020}}</ref> It joined the [[National Health Service]] as Clayton Hospital in 1948.<ref name=na/> After services had transferred to [[Pinderfields Hospital]], it closed in 2012.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.wakefieldexpress.co.uk/news/historic-clayton-hospital-to-close-1-5020650|title=Historic Clayton Hospital to close|newspaper=Wakefield Express|date=12 October 2012|accessdate=28 January 2020}}</ref> A major fire took place at the derelict hospital in February 2017.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.yorkshireeveningpost.co.uk/news/investigation-launched-cause-fire-old-hospital-building-wakefield-604520|title=Investigation launched into cause of fire at old hospital building in Wakefield|newspaper=Yorkshire Evening Post|date=20 February 2017|accessdate=28 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2017 [[Queen Elizabeth Grammar School, Wakefield]] secured planning consent to refurbish the Victorian Tower but demolish the remainder of the buildings to create sports facilities.<ref>{{cite news|url=\nhttps://www-wakefieldexpress-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org/v/s/www.wakefieldexpress.co.uk/news/grammar-school-to-redevelop-the-former-clayton-hospital-1-8663038/amp?amp_js_v=a2&amp_gsa=1&usqp=mq331AQCKAE%3D#aoh=15802919455179&referrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com&amp_tf=From%20%251%24s&ampshare=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wakefieldexpress.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fgrammar-school-to-redevelop-the-former-clayton-hospital-1-8663038|title=Grammar school to redevelop the former Clayton Hospital|date=21 July 2017|newspaper=Wakefield Express|accessdate=28 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:1787 establishments in England]]\n[[Category:Hospital buildings completed in 1879]]\n[[Category:Hospitals in West Yorkshire]]\n[[Category:Defunct hospitals in England]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clayton_Hospital"}
